---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import Nav from "../components/Nav.astro";
import Footer from "../components/Footer.astro";
---

<BaseLayout title="Marten Terms of Service">
  <Nav />
  <main>
    <h1>Terms of Service</h1>
    <div>
      <h2>1. About marten</h2>
      <p>
        marten is an open-source reverse tunnel tool that allows users to expose
        local services to the internet. These Terms of Service ("Terms") govern
        your use of the marten software and the public server hosted at
        usemarten.tech ("the Service").
      </p>
      <h2>2. Acceptance</h2>
      <p>
        By using the Service, you agree to these Terms. If you do not agree, do
        not use the Service.
      </p>
      <h2>3. Who can use the Service</h2>
      <p>
        You must be at least 13 years old to use the Service. By using it, you
        represent that you meet this requirement.
      </p>
      <h2>4. Your responsibilities</h2>
      <p>
        You are solely responsible for:
        <ul>
          <li>Everything that passes through your tunnel</li>
          <li>All content served via your tunnel URL</li>
          <li>
            Ensuring your use of the Service complies with all applicable laws
            in your country and any country where your content is accessed
          </li>
        </ul>
        You agree not to use the Service to:
        <ul>
          <li>Distribute malware, ransomware, or other malicious software</li>
          <li>Host phishing pages or other deceptive content</li>
          <li>Serve illegal content of any kind</li>
          <li>Conduct DDoS attacks or other network abuse</li>
          <li>Infringe any third party's intellectual property rights</li>
          <li>Circumvent security controls of other systems</li>
        </ul>
      </p>
      <h2>5. No responsibility for tunnel content</h2><p>
        marten operates as a passive conduit. It forwards bytes between your
        local service and visitors, without inspecting, modifying, or storing
        the content of those bytes. <strong
          >marten accepts no responsibility whatsoever for any content served
          through any tunnel.</strong
        > The operator of the tunnel (you) is solely and entirely responsible for
        any and all content, services, or data made accessible via your tunnel URL.
        This includes but is not limited to: any harm caused to third parties by content
        served through your tunnel, any legal claims arising from content served through
        your tunnel, and any regulatory violations related to content served through
        your tunnel.
      </p>
      <h2>6. Termination</h2>
      <p>
        We reserve the right to terminate or suspend your access to the Service
        at any time, without notice, for any reason, including but not limited
        to violation of these Terms or conduct that we determine to be harmful
        to other users, third parties, or the Service itself.
      </p>
      <h2>7. Service availability</h2>
      <p>
        Marten is a free, open-source project maintained in spare time. No
        promises are made about uptime, reliability, performance, security, or
        continued availability. The service may go down, change, or disappear at
        any time without notice. You have no entitlement to continued access or
        any particular level of service quality.
      </p>
      <h2>8. Disclaimer of warranties</h2>
      <p>
        THE SERVICE IS PROVIDED "AS IS" AND "AS AVAILABLE," WITHOUT WARRANTY OF
        ANY KIND. TO THE FULLEST EXTENT PERMITTED BY LAW, WE DISCLAIM ALL
        WARRANTIES, EXPRESS OR IMPLIED, INCLUDING WARRANTIES OF MERCHANTABILITY,
        FITNESS FOR A PARTICULAR PURPOSE, AND NON-INFRINGEMENT.
      </p>
      <h2>9. No obligation to anyone</h2>
      <p>
        THE OPERATOR OF USEMARTEN.TECH OWES NOTHING TO ANY USER OF THE SERVICE.
        USE IS ENTIRELY AT YOUR OWN RISK. By using the Service you acknowledge
        that:
        <ul>
          <li>You have no entitlement to continued access</li>
          <li>You have no entitlement to any level of service quality</li>
          <li>
            You have no entitlement to support, assistance, or compensation of
            any kind
          </li>
          <li>
            No relationship of obligation exists between you and the operator
          </li>
        </ul>
      </p>
      <h2>10. Limitation of liability</h2><p>
        TO THE FULLEST EXTENT PERMITTED BY LAW, THE OPERATOR OF USEMARTEN.TECH
        SHALL NOT BE LIABLE FOR ANY DAMAGES OF ANY KIND — DIRECT, INDIRECT,
        INCIDENTAL, SPECIAL, CONSEQUENTIAL, OR PUNITIVE — ARISING OUT OF OR IN
        CONNECTION WITH YOUR USE OF OR INABILITY TO USE THE SERVICE. IN ANY
        CASE, TOTAL LIABILITY SHALL NOT EXCEED €0.
      </p>
      <h2>11. Indemnification</h2><p>
        You agree to defend, indemnify, and hold harmless the operator of marten
        and usemarten.tech from any claims, damages, losses, costs, or expenses
        (including reasonable legal fees) arising out of or related to your use
        of the Service or any content served through your tunnel.
      </p>
      <h2>12. Abuse reporting</h2><p>
        If you believe someone is using the Service to serve illegal or harmful
        content, please report it to: <b>abuse@usemarten.tech</b> We will investigate
        reports and take appropriate action, which may include terminating the relevant
        tunnel.
      </p>
      <h2>13. Changes to these Terms</h2>
      <p>
        We may update these Terms at any time. Continued use of the Service
        after changes constitutes acceptance of the updated Terms.
      </p>
    </div>
  </main>
  <Footer />
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  main {
    max-width: 680px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: 50px 40px 90px;
  }

  h1 {
    font-family: var(--font-space-grotesk);
    font-weight: 300;
    font-size: 40px;
    margin: 0 0 40px;
  }

  h2 {
    font-family: var(--font-space-grotesk);
    font-weight: 400;
    font-size: 20px;
    margin: 0 0 16px;
    padding-top: 40px;
    border-top: 1px solid rgba(244, 232, 214, 0.08);
  }

  h2:first-of-type {
    padding-top: 0;
    border-top: none;
  }

  p {
    font-size: 15px;
    line-height: 1.7;
    color: #d8cbb4;
    margin: 0 0 14px;
  }

  ul {
    font-size: 15px;
    line-height: 1.7;
    color: #d8cbb4;
    padding-left: 20px;
    margin: 10px 0 0;
  }

  li {
    margin-bottom: 6px;
  }

  strong {
    color: #edbb7e;
    font-weight: 600;
  }

  b {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-weight: 400;
    color: #edbb7e;
  }
</style>
